  "title": "Car in mag field",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a cart with a rectangular conducting loop attached to the top of the cart. The loop has area A and resistance R. There is a ramp behind the cart that extends down and to the right to a horizontal surface. The cart is on the horizontal surface moving to the right, at speed v. The cart is moving into a magnetic field, labeled vector B that has width x and is directed out of the page. &nbsp;After the magnetic field is a ramp that extends up and to the right.\" height=\"140\" src=\"/images/751e7b14ddc67b863070dc885c82116a.png\" width=\"500\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A lab cart of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, with a rectangular conducting loop of area <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and resistance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> attached to it, rolls down a ramp onto a horizontal surface of negligible friction and then through an area with uniform magnetic field <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector B\"><math alttext=\"vector B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>→</mo></mrow></mover></mrow></math></span></span>. The cart moves a horizontal distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> while in the field, and then it moves out of the field and up another ramp identical to the first. Which of the following modifications would decrease the height that the cart rolls up the second ramp?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i1",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Increasing the magnetic field strength <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> so that there is a greater change in flux through the loop</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Increasing the horizontal distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of the magnetic field so that there is more time for energy to be transferred out of the cart</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Increasing the mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of the cart so that there is more inertia in the system</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Reversing the direction of the magnetic field <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector B\"><math alttext=\"vector B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>→</mo></mrow></mover></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> in order to create a force that opposes the motion of the cart</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Orienting the area <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of the rectangular loop to be perpendicular to the velocity in order to create the maximum force.</p>",
        "value": "i5"
      }
    ]
  },
